The following procedure takes the adjacency matrix of a simple graph.
function X(G[1..n, 1..n], n)
begin
    B=G*G;
    s=0;
    for i=1 to n-1 do
        for j=i+1 to n do
            if G[i, j]=1 then s=s+B[i, j];
    return s/3;
end
1. What parameter of G does the procedure return?
2. How should it be modified in order for the execution time to be asymptotically as short as possible?
